If I were your co-founder, here’s exactly what I’d do over the next 30 days.

Week 1 — Validate the Idea

Talk to people.

Specifically:

* 10 golfers
* 5 golf course GMs
* 5 pro shop managers
* 2–3 golf bag companies
* 2 embroidery/patch companies

Ask only:

“If your course had an official collectible patch, would people buy it?”

“What price do you think would sell?”

“Would you carry it?”

You’re not selling.

You’re learning.

⸻

Week 2 — Build a Tiny MVP

Forget the bag.

Design:

* 10 fictional course patches
* 10 achievement patches

Examples:

* First Birdie
* Broke 90
* Hole in One
* Sunrise Round
* Walking Warrior
* Local Legend

Then make physical samples.

Hold them.

See if they feel collectible.

⸻

Week 3 — Talk to Courses

Walk into local pro shops.

Bring:

* Sample patches
* One-page concept sheet
* Display mockup

Pitch:

“Imagine every golfer leaving with something they collect forever—not just another logo ball.”

Watch reactions.

⸻

Week 4 — Decide

You’ll know if people light up.

If they don’t…

Pivot.

If they do…

Then think about bags.

